text:
This is my second visit in 2 weeks. Discovered this gem unintentionally. Menu is reasonably priced. Food is delicious and portions are good.
Pomfret fish was meaty and well-cooked. Bean sprouts were fat and juicy with generous amount of salted fish. Nam Yu crispy pork was not dry and tasted good.
Do give this place a try.

Note: Thereâ€™s an opening special of $12 for the steamed pomfret.

Came here to try the KL Hokkien mee. Very tasty. Fried bee hoon also well executed. Ordered also veg & crispy noodles. All very well done. Thumbs up.

Coffeeshop seems quiet but nice friendly staff and comfortable ambience, no need to wait for table.

This tze char stall is situated in a coffeeshop along frankel avenue. You defineitely cant miss the bright neonlight signboard as you drive pass by. If you are driving, parking could be an issue.

Staff were friendly, order were taken and food were served shortly after. Ordered their signature Nonya steam fish, sauce was great, unfortunately fish turn cold fast. The prawn rolls and stir fried royale chives were equally good as well.

Price was reasonable and menu is pretty extensive as well. Can consider coming back again.

Saw the rating quite good and decided to give it a try, after trying, verdict is food were so so, not very fantastic. We order sambal Petai (mentioned by the employee) and we received minced meat with petai, the minced meat is more than Petai.
Toufu also so so.. hot drinks we ordered are not even hot too...
I like the food, today we have take away so the photos are not justifying but they tasted really good. Went to the shop 2 weeks ago and dining in was equally good. Price was reasonable too.
